  <discussion>Eupatorium ×pinnatifidum has been suggested to represent a series of recurrent
        hybrids between E. capillifolium or E. compositifolium and E. perfoliatum; molecular data,
        in addition to confirming that this combination occurs, also show that E. serotinum rather
        than E. perfoliatum is the second parent in at least some plants included in E.
        ×pinnatifidum.</discussion>
